reviewText:
THIS GAME IS A TRAP!

At first i thought of it as just another nepgame with a bunch of cute girls doing silly stuff to save the world with the power of friendship. Guess that's what they wanted me to believe, because then the Conquest route came and ♥♥♥♥ turned real really fast...

Pros:
♥ Conquest Ending;
♥ Unrelated to the first game;
♥ Glorious imoutos at 1080p/60fps;
♥ Stupidly hilarious dialogs;
♥ Short for an JRPG (~30 hours);
♥ Can skip battle animations;
♥ Has some NG+ content;
♥ Multiple endings
♥ Waifu galore;
♥ Gaogaigar;

Cons:
- Conquest route doesn't let me play as the other imoutos;
- Might be a bit grindy;
- Slightly repetitive gameplay;
- NG+ enemies are pathetically weak.
- RED & Compa, DESUUUU.

Conflicted:
¿ Story can get grim, overly emotional and slightly philosophical (some ppl might not like it);
¿ Neptune's dialogs makes her sound like a ♥♥♥♥♥ (fixed by the re-translation mod);
¿ Characters won't STFU in world map, but it's so cute :3
¿ Needs admin rights or it can crash entering dungeons (not really an issue, just tick a box in the .exe);
¿ Gameplay is the same as the other re;birth games, but still much better than the old PS3 games...

Overall score: nepu/64

By far my favourite game, it gave me what I love which is a great game full of Nep, and took away what I hate which are the people who hang around me.

Pros:
-Another great Neptunia game;
-Lots of horrible jokes;
-Lots of Japanese culture;
-People lose respect for you and won't talk to you anymore;
-You jump, you see panties;
-You unlock the jump higher plan, you see more panties;

Cons;
-I cried when I finished everything;
